values.\n\n2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log: The debug log shows that the SLP vectorizer successfully builds and schedules a bundle containing various add instructions,
then proceeds to vectorize a horizontal reduction. The crash happens during the processing of externally used values when trying to map a reduced value back to its
original form.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis: From the debugger inspection, we can see that:\n   - `RdxVal` is `%subi = add i16 0, 0`\n   - `TrackedVals` contains
