18392-18395. However, later in the code (line 18598-18609), the code assumes that any `RdxVal` from `TrackedVals` will have a corresponding entry in
`TrackedToOrig`.\n   \n   The issue is that `%subi` is used as an operand in the reduction chain but was filtered out during the initial candidate selection because
it might have been considered incompatible with other values (possibly due to being a constant-like value or having different opcode characteristics). However, it's
still referenced later when processing externally used values.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\n   + The fix is to check if `RdxVal` exists in `TrackedToOrig` before
calling `at()`. If it doesn't exist, we should skip processing this value or handle it appropriately. Looking at the context, the safest approach is to continue to
